    • Method Detail

      • createCoreVBO

        public static <T extends Buffer> CoreVBO<T> createCoreVBO(CoreGL gl,
                                                          CoreVBO.DataType dataType,
                                                          CoreVBO.UsageType usageType,
                                                          int size)
        Create a new VBO with the given Type containing float data. This will create the buffer object but does not bind or send the data to the GPU. You'll need to call bind() to bind this VBO and you'll need to call send() to transmit the buffer data to the GPU.
        Parameters:
        dataType - the CoreVBO.DataType of the NIO Buffer that the CoreVBO instance should contain
        usageType - the GL usage type for the buffer @see CoreVBO.UsageType
        size - the size of the buffer
        Returns:
        the CoreVBO instance

      • getBuffer

        public T getBuffer()
        Allows access to the internally kept nio Buffer that contains the original buffer data. You can access and change this buffer if you want to update the buffer content. Just make sure that you call rewind() before sending your new data to the GPU with the send() method.
        Returns:
        the Buffer with the original buffer data (stored in main memory not GPU memory)

      • getMappedBuffer

        public T getMappedBuffer()
        Maps the buffer object that this represents into client space and returns the buffer
        Returns:
        the FloatBuffer to directly write data into (mapped into client space but is actual memory on the GPU)

      • unmapBuffer

        public void unmapBuffer()
        You'll need to call that when you're done writing data into a mapped buffer to return access back to the GPU.
